His combat experiences span from the violent streets of Fallujah, Iraq; to the Al-Qaeda stronghold of Marjah, Afghanistan during Operation: Moshtarak. Mr. May has a very strong infantry combat background as he was a squad leader during Operation: Moshtarak and was tasked with controlling key parts of the city, trainings soldiers of the Afghanistan National Army and Afghanistan National Police, as well as fighting against a well trained enemy in their own back yard. The Urban Carry offers quick access to your firearm.  Simply pull the flap and the handle of your firearm is easily exposed. With only the magnetic flap exposed the only people who will know that you are carrying in an urban environment are the other people with an Urban Carry.  Our other main focus was to build the concealed carry holster for comfort. Most Inside Waistband holsters have the handle of the firearm on the waistline.  Any movement will cause the handle to push into your stomach, side or back while the barrel may push into your leg. This makes carrying a firearm uncomfortable for many people.  As a result many simply won't carry all the time. That's what we wanted to avoid. With the Urban Carry, the holster rides about an inch below the waistline which puts your firearm parallel to your leg. This way you have full mobility without hardly ever feeling your firearm. So long as your pants are worn comfortably (sorry, no skinny-jeans) then we are confident you'll be able to sit at a desk or your car all day without any discomfort from your firearm. The Urban Carry also has a place in the back to keep your concealed license, a credit card or some extra cash to make sure you always have that at hand. With this particular design it is very unlikely that you'll ever drop or expose your firearm or have it stolen. The Urban Carry is proudly made in the United States of America with 100% genuine saddle grade leather. title: For Sale:  P38 AC/45 Walther - SOLD
postcontent: Rare vintage variation late war Walther P38 "ac45" with dark brown bakelite grips in very good condition. The right side of the slide of this 1945 P38 has the eagle over the WaA359 Inspection/Acceptance (E/WaA359) mark flanking both sides of the military test fire proof mark - the eagle over the swastika in the center. And the left side of the slide has the P38 designation, the s/n "28xx b" followed by the "ac 45" manufacturer code.Out of over a million P38s produced, Walther only produced roughly 31,000 P38s marked "ac 45" and very few of those returned from the battlefield - so they are far more rare than previous years when production rates ranged as high as 150,000 units per year. This is an authentic 1945 Walther P38 with all matching serial numbers on the frame, slide, under barrel and locking block. S/N: 28xx b. The alphabetic character following the s/n, indicates the manufacturing block or group of P38s. The "c" block of pistols were never completed due to the war ending, so the "b" block pistols, such as this one, were the last full block of Walther P38s. It is very reasonably priced for a nice condition late war very rare Walther "ac 45" P38 with a clean barrel and all matching S/Ns.  Refer to the attached photos and contact with questions. Competitively priced at $1050.
